                <note rend="inline" type="source">714.1515/684: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Geissler</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-05-25T11:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 25, 1928—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>45. Your 69, May 23, 7:00 P.M. second paragraph. Mr. Davis has reported that he
                    discussed various possible boundary lines with <pb facs="0874" n="746"
                        xml:id="pg_746"/> the Guatemalan and Honduran Commissioners in the hope of
                    finding a basis upon which they might establish a boundary by mutual accord but
                    that he never formally proposed as mediator any of the lines that were
                    discussed.</p>
                <p>The Department hopes that this will be made perfectly clear in any statements
                    which the Guatemalan Government may make with regard to the boundary
                    conference.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
